args: Come to think of it, Grimnir's been with us\nfor a while now. Is he settling in all right?
He seems to be getting on well enough.
What she said. Oh, and Aldred swung\nby the castle a little while ago and...
My left arm throbs...\nDamn you, Syndicate monsters.
Do my ears deceive me?\nDare I believe?!
Have I found the bearer of a kindred soul?!
My right arm throbs... The souls of\ntwo score hundred demons sealed\nwithin it seethe.
What are you supposed to be? Leave my\nsight, before this accursed wyrmbinding in\nmy left arm rages beyond my control!
Heh, then we two share the same burden.\nI am the war-god, Grimnir. Let us swear a\nforbidden oath, here and now!
What are you—*gasp* No!\nAre you with the Syndicate?!
Start talking! You'll tell me all you know,\nor the abomination I harbor within will\ndrag it out of you!
WYRMBINDING! Feel the brunt of my\naccursed power—ngah?! Can't...control!
Yes...YES! I TOTALLY get that!\nArms are the WORST!
Two abyssal souls, brought together\nnow by fate, resonate and echo forth!
It looked like they were getting\nalong great!
Yeesh... Speaking of Grimnir, he had\na run-in with Malora the other day.
Ooh, what have we here? A fresh recruit?
I am the war-god, heaven sent.\nMy name...is Grimnir.
I have alighted upon fair Alberia tasked\nwith nothing less than saving the world\nfrom destruction.
You would dare cross the threshold of,\nuh...
Personal space! You're very close, Miss!
Ah ha ha! Look at you blushing. Still new\nto all this? That only makes you cuter.
I know a guy who insists on getting close,\nbut this feels more threatening!
Good to see him getting...friendly?\nWith the others? If we can call it that.
At the very least, he's begun to settle in.
Is it, though? Ah, well.\nIt's no skin off my wings. ♪\n...Ew, phrasing, Notte.
I think he's on watch duty out east today.\nWhy?
Aw, he's working? I was gonna ask to\nplay with him again.
Yeah! He uses his wind to float you up in\nthe air.
It's awesome! You should come try it too,\n{player_name}!
That does sound like fun. Unfortunately, it\nwill have to wait for another time when he\nisn't on duty.
Nah. I got this one, you guys.\nI'll go swap shifts with him.
The new kid's makin' friends.\nHow's a guy NOT gonna encourage that?
Hee hee, thank you! You're the best,\nRanzal. Now, c'mon! Let's all go together!
Aha ha ha! This is great!
Hey, now. Don't go wiggling around too\nmuch up there. I don't want you falling!
Heh. He doesn't come across as the most\nreliable fellow, but he's comfortable in the\nbig-brother role around the little ones.
Yes. I'm relieved to see him so at home\nhere.
No, it is as you say—he does seem to\nhave settled in. But...just between us...
He's such a curious case. Take that wind.
Mind you, I have no proof of what I'm\nabout to venture. Honestly, I'm not even\ncertain it's possible...
But his mana suggests that he may not\nbe human at all. And mana doesn't lie.
He certainly looks the part, so I'd never\nthought to question it.
What do you suspect he might be, if not\nhuman?
I couldn't say. He's clearly not a sylvan,\nnor a rokkan or qilin.
I sense from him a mana I've never felt\nbefore.
Something...vast. In the realm of the gods\nhe claims to walk among.
The war-god, Grimnir...\nJust who is he, really?
